# Testing

## Structure
```
tests/
  unit/domain/          # pure domain logic — no DB, no HTTP
  integration/api/      # real DB + Redis via ASGI client
  conftest.py           # shared fixtures (JWT secret)
  integration/conftest.py  # engine, http_client, truncate_users
```

## Reference tests
- **Unit**: `tests/unit/domain/test_user_entity.py` — test domain entities/VOs in isolation
- **Integration**: `tests/integration/api/test_users_flow.py` — full HTTP flow with real DB

## Conventions
- All test code and docstrings in **English**
- Use `pytest.mark.asyncio` for async tests
- Integration fixtures use `scope="session"` for the DB engine; per-test truncation via `autouse`
- Skip integration tests gracefully when DB is unreachable: `pytest.skip(...)`
- Assert status codes explicitly: `assert resp.status_code == 200, resp.text`
- Name test functions: `test_<what>_<condition>` e.g. `test_register_duplicate_email_returns_409`

## Running tests
```bash
export PYTHONPATH=src
poetry run pytest tests/unit -v                  # no DB needed
poetry run pytest tests/integration -v           # requires docker compose up -d
make test                                        # both suites
```

## Adding tests for a new entity
1. Unit test in `tests/unit/domain/test_<entity>.py` — validate business rules
2. Integration test in `tests/integration/api/test_<entity>s_flow.py` — CRUD via HTTP
3. Add `truncate_<entity>s` autouse fixture in `tests/integration/conftest.py`
